    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.6.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo (lua related)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nx86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nxterm 372\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nArch official community repo\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\necho \"vim.opt.wildchar = \\\"<c-z>\\\"\" > test_init.lua\r\nnvim -u ./test_init.lua\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim starts and the value of wildchar is set to \"<c-z>\"\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nNeovim greets with error message upon start:\r\n\r\n> Error detected while processing /home/jscandal/test_init.lua:\r\nE5113: Error while calling lua chunk: vim/_meta.lua:324: Invalid option type 'string' for 'wildchar', should be number\r\nstack traceback:\r\n        [C]: in function 'error'\r\n        vim/_meta.lua:324: in function 'assert_valid_value'\r\n        vim/_meta.lua:393: in function 'convert_value_to_vim'\r\n        vim/_meta.lua:681: in function '_set'\r\n        vim/_meta.lua:724: in function '__newindex'\r\n        ./test_init.lua:1: in main chunk\r\nPress ENTER or type command to continue\r\n\r\n\r\n",
